If you don't want to pay Old San Juan prices, but want to be close to all the activities this is a great option.	The prices are low and for that price the rooms are comfortable, clean and updated, the lobby is nice, nice pool, great location, and friendly staff.	We stayed for one night pre-cruise and used points to pay for the room so the price was right.	This hotel lured me to book with it with its relatively lower price, nice photos, and good reviews.	None of these are deal-breakers, but I thought the price of $200 a night was a little high (it felt like a $120 hotel).